            "generated_answer": "## Solution\n\nTo calculate the year-over-year change in operating income from FY2015 to FY2016, I'll use the operating income figures from the income statement.\n\n### Step 1: Identify Operating Income Values\n\n- **FY2016 Operating Income:** $1,493,602 thousand\n- **FY2015 Operating Income:** $903,095 thousand\n\n### Step 2: Calculate Year-over-Year Change\n\n$$\\text{YoY Change} = \\frac{\\text{FY2016 Operating Income} - \\text{FY2015 Operating Income}}{\\text{FY2015 Operating Income}} \\times 100$$\n\n$$\\text{YoY Change} = \\frac{1,493,602 - 903,095}{903,095} \\times 100$$\n\n$$\\text{YoY Change} = \\frac{590,507}{903,095} \\times 100$$\n\n$$\\text{YoY Change} = 0.6539 \\times 100 = \\textbf{65.4\\%}$$\n\n### Result\n\nAdobe's operating income grew by **65.4%** from FY2015 to FY2016.",
