            "gold_answer": "-3.7",
            "generated_answer": "I'll calculate the FY2019 Cash Conversion Cycle (CCC) for General Mills step by step.\n\n## Data Collection from Financial Statements\n\n**Income Statement (FY2019):**\n- Net Sales (Revenue): $16,865.2M\n- Cost of Sales (COGS): $11,108.4M\n\n**Balance Sheet:**\n- Inventory FY2019: $1,559.3M\n- Inventory FY2018: $1,642.2M\n- Accounts Receivable FY2019: $1,679.7M\n- Accounts Receivable FY2018: $1,684.2M\n- Accounts Payable FY2019: $2,854.1M\n- Accounts Payable FY2018: $2,746.2M\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: Calculate DIO (Days Inventory Outstanding)\n\n**Average Inventory** = (1,559.3 + 1,642.2) / 2 = **1,600.75M**\n\n**DIO** = 365 \u00d7 1,600.75 / 11,108.4 = **52.60 days**\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Calculate DSO (Days Sales Outstanding)\n\n**Average Accounts Receivable** = (1,679.7 + 1,684.2) / 2 = **1,681.95M**\n\n**DSO** = 365 \u00d7 1,681.95 / 16,865.2 = **36.40 days**\n\n---\n\n## Step 3: Calculate DPO (Days Payable Outstanding)\n\n**Average Accounts Payable** = (2,854.1 + 2,746.2) / 2 = **2,800.15M**\n\n**Change in Inventory** = 1,559.3 - 1,642.2 = **-82.9M**\n\n**Denominator** = COGS + Change in Inventory = 11,108.4 + (-82.9) = **11,025.5M**\n\n**DPO** = 365 \u00d7 2,800.15 / 11,025.5 ",
