            "generated_answer": "I need to find:\n1. Net income attributable to General Mills shareholders (FY2022)\n2. Total cash dividends paid (FY2022)\n\n**From the Consolidated Statements of Earnings (Chunk 1):**\n- Net earnings attributable to General Mills = **$2,707.3 million**\n\n**From the Consolidated Statements of Cash Flows (Chunk 1):**\n- Dividends paid are not explicitly shown in Chunk 1 for FY2022, but I can use the dividends per share information.\n\nLooking at Chunk 1 for the Cash Flow statement, the financing activities section is cut off. However, from Chunk 2 (FY2020 data), dividends paid = $1,195.8 million.\n\nFrom the income statement (Chunk 1):\n- Dividends per share FY2022 = $2.04\n- Dividends per share FY2021 = $2.02\n- Dividends per share FY2020 = $1.96\n\nUsing EPS basic FY2022 = $4.46, and dividends per share = $2.04:\n\n**Retention Ratio = (Net Income - Dividends Paid) / Net Income**\n\nUsing dividends per share / EPS as the payout ratio:\n- Payout Ratio = $2.04 / $4.46 = 0.4574\n\n- **Retention Ratio = 1 - Payout Ratio = 1 - 0.4574 = 0.5426**\n\nAlternatively, using diluted EPS = $4.42:\n- Payout Ratio = $2.04 / $4.42 = 0.4615\n- Retention Ratio = 1 - 0.4615 = 0.5385\n\nUsing the **basic EPS** approach:\n\n**Retention Ratio = 1 - (2.04/4.46) = 1 - 0.4574 \u2248 0.54**\n\n---\n\n**The FY2022 Retention Ratio for General Mills is approximately 0.54 (or 54%).**",
